Dunlending Elder x1<br />
Death to the Strawheads x2<br />
Dark Fury x2<br />
Wild Man Raid x1<br />
War Cry of Dunland x1<br />
Iron Axe x3    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The Strategy of this deck is to always go second.<br />
If you are playing one on one the bid zero burdens. If you are playing with three or four people then make sure that you go second. This is<br />
Important because of site 2 and 3. Since Dunland men usually die during archery phase it is crucial that they survive the early turns (sort of like a surprise attack).<br />
As far as free peoples go, this deck is very good at keeping good movement in your hand. Since almost every event card is a strength bonus, you can use a lot of them, keeping a good flow of cards. I put a duplicate of Faramir and<br />
Denethor in the deck, again, to promote hand movement.<br />
Since there are already five companions in the starting fellowship, the strategy is to eventually sacrifice smeagol and replace him with a stronger companion. Until he is sacrificed, draw all archery fire toward him and Frodo (they most likely will not get exhausted from just archery fire).<br />
Also, exert Smeagol to heal Frodo whenever you want. I suggest that after Smeagol dies, you replace him with Boromir (because you will still be able to heal Frodo, or give him a strength bonus). Once Smeagol is replaced, do not play any more companions until sites 6-9. At that time play 1 or 2 companions.<br />
If it is not time to play another companion but you have two or three in your hand, discard the weaker one during the regroup phase.<br />
Finaly, I suggest that you get a Hobbit Sword on Frodo then let him participate in skirmishes (using Boromir&#39;s special ability if neccesary).    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
